Package: synesthR
Title: Generate Synchronized Images and Music from Literary Text
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Raban", "Heller", email = "raban.heller@charite.de",
    role = c("aut", "cre"), comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-8006-9742"))
Description: Extracts linguistic features from literary text in German, English,
    and French, including a sentence-level sentiment arc, lexical diversity,
    rhythm, and punctuation density, and maps them deterministically onto
    visual and musical parameters. From a single shared feature score it
    renders a generative still image and a synchronized audio waveform, so
    that the picture and the music are two views of the same analysis. Colour
    palettes and 'ggplot2' themes can be extracted not only from text but from
    images and audio through a common interface, and media objects (text,
    image, audio, score) are passed between functions through a shared
    interchange container. An optional assistive layer can interpret results
    using a locally running large language model.
